The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 January is 34,343 (3,975 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 January, there were 3,525 new confirmed cases (408.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 January, there were 4,601 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (1,076 fewer cases).
